 and monthly meetings with the Chief</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> Constable and his Chief Officer team. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I believe the Constabulary’s crime recording to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">be good</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">, it was judged as such by Her Majesty’s Inspectorate of Constabulary in 2010 and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> look forward to a further inspection of crime recording in the New Year.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> I have also commissioned a piece of work to be undertaken by the </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Audit Committee </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">which will </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">review</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> the integrity of crime recording practices in Cheshire and provide me with additional reassurance that standards are being properly applied. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 18pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">December 2013</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>